ChannelId.Description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the contact channel.

RetryIntervalInMinutes.Description: The number of minutes to wait to retry sending engagement in the case the engagement initially fails.

ContactId.Description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the contact.

IsEssential.Description: A Boolean value determining if the contact's acknowledgement stops the progress of stages in the plan.

DurationInMinutes.Description: The time to wait until beginning the next stage.

RotationIds.Description: List of Rotation Ids to associate with Contact

Targets.Description: The contacts or contact methods that the escalation plan or engagement plan is engaging.

Alias.Description: Alias of the contact. String value with 20 to 256 characters. Only alphabetical, numeric characters, dash, or underscore allowed.

Arn.Description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the contact.

DisplayName.Description: Name of the contact. String value with 3 to 256 characters. Only alphabetical, space, numeric characters, dash, or underscore allowed.

Plan.Description: The stages that an escalation plan or engagement plan engages contacts and contact methods in.

Type.Description: Contact type, which specify type of contact. Currently supported values: ?PERSONAL?, ?SHARED?, ?OTHER?.

Arn.Description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the engagement to a contact channel.

ChannelAddress.Description: The details that SSM Incident Manager uses when trying to engage the contact channel.

ChannelName.Description: The device name. String of 6 to 50 alphabetical, numeric, dash, and underscore characters.

ChannelType.Description: Device type, which specify notification channel. Currently supported values: ?SMS?, ?VOICE?, ?EMAIL?, ?CHATBOT.

DeferActivation.Description: If you want to activate the channel at a later time, you can choose to defer activation. SSM Incident Manager can't engage your contact channel until it has been activated.

ChannelId.Description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the contact channel.

RetryIntervalInMinutes.Description: The number of minutes to wait to retry sending engagement in the case the engagement initially fails.

ContactId.Description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the contact.

IsEssential.Description: A Boolean value determining if the contact's acknowledgement stops the progress of stages in the plan.

DurationInMinutes.Description: The time to wait until beginning the next stage.

Targets.Description: The contacts or contact methods that the escalation plan or engagement plan is engaging.

Arn.Description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the contact.

ContactId.Description: Contact ID for the AWS SSM Incident Manager Contact to associate the plan.

RotationIds.Description: Rotation Ids to associate with Oncall Contact for engagement.

Stages.Description: The stages that an escalation plan or engagement plan engages contacts and contact methods in.

DayOfMonth.Description: The day of the month when monthly recurring on-call rotations begin.

DailySettings.Description: Information about on-call rotations that recur daily.

MonthlySettings.Description: Information about on-call rotations that recur monthly.

RecurrenceMultiplier.Description: The number of days, weeks, or months a single rotation lasts.

ShiftCoverages.Description: Information about the days of the week included in on-call rotation coverage.

WeeklySettings.Description: Information about on-call rotations that recur weekly.

CoverageTimes.Description: Information about when an on-call shift begins and ends.

Key.Description: The key name of the tag

Arn.Description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the rotation.

StartTime.Description: Start time of the first shift of Oncall Schedule

TimeZoneId.Description: TimeZone Identifier for the Oncall Schedule
